column24: 'There are serious lack of psychotherapy training in psychiatry curriculum. Although there are 4 months for it but it''s like drop in the sea. We are only introduce with some basic statements about psychodynamic psychotherapy. If we want to learn psychotherapy we must to do it outside residency and pay for it by ourselves. I think that psychotherapy is extremely important in my clinical work in order to better understand and help patients.'
column68: 'I hope step by step we will improve psychotherapy learning situation in Europe!'

column24: 'Psychiatry and psychotherapy are quite close. There are many situations when psychoterapeutic knowledge and practice is very important for a psychiatrist.'

column24: 'Psychotherapy helps to understand your patient much better: why this patient has these symptoms at this moment. It''s not about reducing symptoms only
column25: it''s about teaching the patient new way (thinking or behaving) to cope the problems  himself. Sharing information with patient helps him understand himself better
column26: and be more attentive to himself'
